chunk_content: T E S All index testing services must meet WHO’s 5C minimum standards, including consent, counseling, T confidentiality, correct test results, and connection to person-centered HIV prevention and treatment I N services. Additionally, all index clients should be screened for Intimate Partner Violence (IPV) per WHO G guidelines. An index client should never feel as if she/he/they are required to provide contacts in order to receive any services. Overall, all index testing services being offered at all PEPFAR-supported sites should adhere to PEPFAR’s guidance for implementing safe and ethical index testing services. Note: The reporting of HTS_INDEX data by an implementing partner should not be used to infer whether a partner has conducted index testing in a manner compliant with PEPFAR’s guidance for implementing safe and ethical index testing services.
